name: Dof T-Shirt Women Eggplant
description:
We are proud to introduce our new range of T-shirts featuring innovative Senegalese slogans and messaging! The shirts are exclusive to Baaba Maal's site and shows and are produced on a lovely Bamboo & cotton blend which is VERY soft and produces a great slim fit.
DOF is Wolof for stoopid, in case you were wondering! This is a very unique t-shirt indeed!

name: Mansour Seck, Cisse Diamba Kanoute, Kauding Cissoko Bundle
description: Buy the new Mansour Seck album and complete your collection with Cissè Diamba Kanoute's The East Wind and Kaouding Cissoko's Kora Revolution - three gems from the  contemporary African music scene. All available now for only £20 in a special time limited offer.

name: Kauding Sissoko - Kora Revolution - CD
description: Kaouding Cissoko uses the majestic kora (the 21-string harp-lute) to reveal the full spectrum of the ancient instrument's melody and timbre. Baaba Maal lends his voice to two tracks while backing musicians (inc Cisse Kanoute) from Cissoko's family add vocals, djembe, tama, acoustic bass, guitar and balafon. Track List 1- Kana Kassi 2- Kora Revolution 3- Hero 4- Niani Bagne Na 5- Douwayra Podor 6- Anna 7- Kounoun 8- Saya Djangaro 9- Ditax Kora 10- Senegal- Mauritanie 11- Bannaya

name: Cisse Diamba Kanoute - The East Wind - CD
description: The East Wind alerts the world to the arrival of a major new talent. Cissè Diamba Kanoute has delivered an album of depth and maturity bulging with excellent songs and great playing from some of West Africa’s finest. Her voice has the gravitas of Nina Simone or Dorothy Morrison and from the mbalax of the 1st track Serigne Saliou to the trancey Fourou Mouso Ignile or Baba Sora it becomes clear that this is modern music from next generation of Senegalese talent. Track List 1- Serigne Saliou 2- Kanmiri 3- Poula Soussagathie 4- Toungua 5- El Hadji Mamba 6- M'bacoumba 7- Forou Mouso Ignile 8- Sadio Mady 9- Sabadou 10- Baba Sora

name: Mansour Seck - Teddungal - CD
description: Mansour Seck, Halpular griot, presents his latest work with the help of his long-time collaborator Baaba Maal. The 14 track album was created with 29 musicians in Senegal this year and is exclusively imported and made available on Baabamaa.tv. This is a great work by a legendary musician. A must-have for world music fans. Mansour SECK, griot de la communaute des halpular met dans le marche son dernier opus avec la participation de son jumeau Baaba MAAL. Album de 14 titres interprétés avec vingt neuf musiciens dont le rappeur Paco ...Lenol. Tendunggal SPECIAL OFFER: buy this with Cissè Diamba Kanoute's The East Wind and Kaouding Cissoko's Kora Revolution for only £20 Track List 1- Diaarama ( feat Baaba Maal) 2- Halaybe ( feat Baaba Maal) 3- Bibbe Soxnabe Fouta 4- Maaka Leyo 5- Mbegnou 6- Ndiaatigue 7- Soukanaba 8- Polel 9- Diaarore ( feat Baaba Maal) 10- Filio 11- Dialowaali ( feat Pac Lenol) 12- Ngawlagou 13- Koumanie 14- Guede

name: Television - CD
description: Baaba Maal's latest studio album Television, featuring Brazilian Girls. Track List 1- Television 2- Tindo 3- Miracle 4- Cantaloupe 5- A Song For Women 6- International 7- Dakar Moo 8- Tindo Quando

name: On the Road- CD
description: The raw emotional edge of Baaba Maal's live performances is showcased on the eight tracks featured on this album. Track List 1- Baayo 2- Fanta 3- Farba 4- Iyango 5- Koni - Baaba Maal, Ernest Ranglin 6- Africans Unite (Yolela) 7- Cherie 8- Bamba

name: On the Road - Limited Edition- Vinyl
description: The raw emotional edge of Baaba Maal's live performances is showcased on the eight tracks featured on this album. Only 300 copies of this limited edition LP were manufactured. Each one is hand-numbered and sure to be a collector's item! Track List 1- Baayo 2- Fanta 3- Farba 4- Iyango 5- Koni - Baaba Maal, Ernest Ranglin 6- Africans Unite (Yolela) 7- Cherie 8- Bamba

name: Baayo - CD
description: The first major label release for Baaba Maal. A set of spare, powerful tracks that meld his expressive voice with the unique instrumentation of West Africa. An excellent introduction to contemporary West African music. Track List 1- Baayo 2- Mariama 3- Joulowo 4- Diahowo 5- Baaba 6- Bouyel 7- Yero Mama 8- Agouyadji 9- Dogata 10- Samba

name: Lam Toro - CD
description: Baaba Maal was one of the first African artists who sought to create a thoroughly international music. In mixing traditional Fulani rhythms with reggae and rock he creates here a powerful new sound that excited dancefloors and irritated purists in equal measure. This was both a challenging and progressive album. Track List 1- Hamady Boiro (Yelle) 2- Daande Lenol 3- Lem Gi (Le Miel) 4- Ndelorel 5- Yela 6- Toro (Tioulel l'Oiseau) 7- Daniibe (Les Exilés) 8- Olel (I'écho) 9- Sy Sawande 10- Hamady Bogle

name: Nomad Soul - CD
description: Global African pop, this album features collaborations with reggae star Luciano, the Screaming Orphans, and production by Simon Emerson (Afro-Celt Sound System, Brian Eno, Howie B and others). Track List 1- Souka Nayo (I Will Follow You) 6:24 2- Africans Unite (Yolela) 3:40 3- Mbolo 5:45 4- Cherie 7:07 5- Fanta 4:58 6- Guelel 6:13 7- Douwayra 4:12 8- Iawa 5:09 9- Yiriyaro (Percussion Storm) 4:52 10- Koni 6:26 11- Lam Lam 12:18

name: Missing You - CD
description: Recorded in Africa with the assistance of producer John Leckie (Radiohead and the Stone Roses). A record that captures the gentle beauty of "acoustic Africa". One of Q Magazine's 50 Best Albums of 2001. Track List 1- Yoolelle Maman 2- Miyaabele 3- Fa Laay Fanaan 4- Leydi Ma 5- Jamma Jenngi 6- Fanta 7- Laare Yoo 8- Senegaale Ngummee 9- Mamadi 10- Kowoni Maayo Mi Yeewni 11- Allah Addu Jam

name: Djam Leelii - CD
description: Recorded in 1982 and originally released in 1984, Djam Leelii reappears in 1998 with all its graceful glory intact--and a little added on. Adorned with three previously unheard remastered tracks from the original sessions, this atmospheric masterpiece is carried along by the complementary voices and guitars of Baaba Maal and Mansour Seck, two of West Africa's leading lights. A sense of mystery permeates this classic of acoustic world music. --Steven Stolder Track List 1- Lam Tooro 2- Loodo 3- Muudo Hormo 4- Salminanam 5- Maacina Tooro 6- Djam Leelii 7- Bibbe Leydy 8- Sehilam 9- Kettodee 10- Ko Wone Mayo 11- Daande Lenol 4:34 $0.99 12- Taara

name: Jim Palmer- Remember Makes You - CD
description:
Jim Palmer is a featured artist in Baaba Maal's band and was the opening act for his 2009 European tour.

This new 4 track EP ‘Remember Makes You” includes the previously unreleased tracks Night I fell, A Stone’s Throw Away, Nah Nah and Miya Miya, featuring vocals by Baaba Maal.

name: Live at the Royal Festival Hall - DVD
description: Recorded July 13, 1998 at London's Royal Festival Hall, this was one of the first concerts filmed, recorded and mixed specifically for DVD. Six digital cameras shot the performance; the sound was recorded with 48-track digital equipment. "Live" captures one of the world's most exciting performers in top form and features Jamaican guitar virtuoso Ernest Ranglin.

name: A Voice for Africa - DVD
description: 'A Voice For Africa' is a 60 minute documentary which follows Baaba Maal on a journey from his home village of Podor to a wild late-night concert over the border in Mauritania including performances, interviews, and journeys through Senegal’s spectacular landscape, culture and arts.

name: Palm World Voices- Baaba Maal - Box-Set
description: The life and music of this influential and groundbreaking musician are explored in this CD/DVD package. The CD includes many of his most important songs while the DVD features a full-length documentary, following Baaba Maal on a journey from his home village of Podor to a wild late-night concert over the border in Mauretania. A beautifully designed and compiled package for fans both new and old
